{"name": "Number7 Open Edition 1", "description": "What's a (natural) number? What does it look like? 

Not a number's symbol, like 3, III, Y# or N. Not an object with a numeric property ("squares have 4 sides").

Number7 is a creative interpretation of the number 7, based on von Neumann's construction of natural numbers. Each circle represents a set. Empty circles are empty sets. Think of the artwork as 7's blueprint: An elegant, simple and easy to understand construction with fractal properties.

**[Number9, Open Edition's page](https://zora.co/collections/0xf900551516d983847e37ab2273799442a574d543)** has more details on the concept and ideas behind the collection.

Distributed under CC0. Let's spread an idea worth spreading beyond mathematicians. ", "image": "ipfs://bafybeihi64rs65ddmus7s7aqzcqds3fpw5jd4tqwi5mcc6ftqxjymhloze", "properties": {"number": 1, "name": "Number7 Open Edition"}}
